# LD example setup

LD examples under `packages/modelviewer.dev/examples/ld_*/` use shared styles based on [Tailwind UI](https://tailwindui.com/) patterns.

## Required `<head>` assets

```html
<link type="text/css" href="../../styles/examples.css" rel="stylesheet" />
<link type="text/css" href="../../styles/docs.css" rel="stylesheet" />
<style type="text/tailwindcss"></style>
<script src="../../styles/ld-ui-loader.js" data-href="../../styles/ld-ui.css"></script>
<script src="https://unpkg.com/@tailwindcss/browser@4"></script>
```

Set `<body class="ld">` so docs-site overrides in `examples.css` do not clash with Tailwind controls.

The empty `<style type="text/tailwindcss">` plus `ld-ui-loader.js` is required: the Tailwind Play CDN only processes inline `text/tailwindcss` blocks. The loader fetches `ld-ui.css` into that block before the CDN script runs.

## When to use `ld-*` classes

Use `ld-*` for interactive controls (sliders, buttons, forms, toggles) or viewport status readouts. Prefer `ld-*` over long inline Tailwind strings. Add shared patterns to [`ld-ui.css`](../../packages/modelviewer.dev/styles/ld-ui.css).

## Conventions

- **Tailwind UI** is the visual source of truth
- **Light mode only** — no `dark:*` classes
- **Blue accents** (`blue-600`, `blue-500`) for focus/active — never indigo
- **No Heroicons** — unicode (e.g. `▾` for select chevrons) or emoji
- **Range sliders** — `.ld-range`; do not restyle unless repo-wide design change
